    <h1>Mashreq Bank Credit Card Details</h1><div class="card">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Mashreq Bank offers a range of credit cards tailored for shopping, travel, cashback, and lifestyle benefits.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Up to 55 days of interest-free credit</li>
    <li>Flexible payment options</li>
    <li>Exclusive offers and discounts</li>
    <li>Rewards and cashback programs</li>
    <li>Free airport lounge access with select cards</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Minimum monthly salary: AED 5,000 (varies by card)</li>
    <li>UAE resident</li>
    <li>Age: 21 years and above</li>
    <li>Salaried or self-employed</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>Required Documents</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Copy of valid Emirates ID</li>
    <li>Copy of passport with residence visa page</li>
    <li>Salary certificate (dated within the last 30 days)</li>
    <li>Bank statement (last 3–6 months)</li>
    <li>Trade license (if self-employed)</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>How to Apply</h2>
  <p>Visit the <a href="https://www.mashreqbank.com" target="_blank">official Mashreq Bank website</a> or visit a nearby branch. You can also apply via their mobile app.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>Compare Cards</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Platinum Elite Card:</strong> Best for frequent travelers, with lounge access and travel insurance.</li>
    <li><strong>Smart Saver Card:</strong> Great for cashback on groceries, fuel, and utility bills.</li>
    <li><strong>Noor Credit Card:</strong> Shariah-compliant with flexible payment options.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

